                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4205: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-30T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 30, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Your No. 63, June 30, noon. I have today presented the following letter to
                    the Belgian Ambassador: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I hasten to acknowledge with deep appreciation your communication of
                            today’s date, in which you advise this Government that the Belgian
                            Government has welcomed the President’s proposal, and that the Belgian
                            Government, true to the spirit of cooperation which has always existed
                            between the two countries, is ready to go forward with the President in
                            this effort to promote harmony and reestablish confidence, and to
                            forward the return of the world to economic stability.</p>
                        <p>“The American Government is much gratified to have this evidence of
                            Belgium’s acceptance of the President’s proposal in the spirit in which
                            it was made.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The above will appear in to-morrow morning’s newspapers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
